name: Reflections on the River of Forgetting
Little Nightingale, Take Wing for Tomorrow
The Returnees Never Return
desc: See if you can find the lady Sally mentioned
detail: Ms Sally seems to be worrying about a lady she cares for. If you encounter this lady, you can perhaps help her out.

name: The Gone Girl
desc: Help Elsa find her daughter Annie
detail:
Ms Elsa's only daughter, Annie, went missing.
Keep an eye out for anyone who might be Annie when you're in Icelake.

name: Clock No More Ticking
desc:
Complete any Phoxhunter Commission 
(Can accept this commission via the Commission page)
detail:
You agreed to work with Wells on the commission.
Get ready and go with him.

name: Far Beyond the Sea
desc: Head to Purgatorio Island
detail:
Through your conversation, you learn that Brunetto  like you  once came from Purgatorio Island. He left as a young man, chasing tales of the wider world, never expecting that a single boat ride to the Empire would cost him his way home. In the years since, he has survived by trading in stories and false hopes.
When you tell him what became of Purgatorio Island, something stirs deep within him. If you have the chance, go back for him. Find the home he left behind  and bring back something that might ease this ache of nostalgia.

name: Inspiration Stealer
desc: Talk to Buck
detail:
As a playwright, Mr Buck is never stingy with his rhetorical flourishes, showcasing his literary prowess as a professional playwright.
Right now, though, it seems Mr Buck is in dire need of a translator rather than applause. Try to make sense of his elaborate dictions.

name: To Those You Miss
desc: Have a chat with Emma
detail: Emma, the student presenting flowers, seems preoccupied. While she's alone and lost in thought, it might be a good time to ask what's on her mind.

name: The Unseen Horns
desc: Talk to Faye
detail: In Icelake, you notice a Sola girl who seems to believe she's a Charon. Might be worth checking out.

name: The Bloodstained Stones
desc: Report to Kevin
detail:
Near Icelake, you notice a miner looking visibly uneasy, a sack of ore stained with something that might be blood lying beside him.
The whole situation feels off. Report it to Kevin, one of the Escort soldiers stationed at the city gate  it's the safest move.

name: Hello, Icelake
desc: Investigate the backstories of the 3 things you got from Margie
detail:
As Margie said, things that seem worthless can sometimes hold great value. Even the rubbish bins scattered around the city might hide untold stories.
The 3 items you got from Margie: a prescription, a box of paper stars, and a key, each one holds a mystery of its own. Follow the clues showed on these 3 things to uncover the stories behind them!

name: Dedicated Chef
desc: Go fishing
detail: Cast your line and reel in a Phoxenetrout for Marcus. This time, he's after a particular flavour  let's hope the dish hits the mark.

name: How the Team Got Its Name
episode: How the Team Got Its Name

name: Sewer Carnival
desc: Speak with Dutton in the sewers
detail: A free "ride" in the sewers? It all sounds rather dubious... but Dutton seems oddly confident. Since it's free, might as well humour him and see what he's cooked up.

name: Little Researcher
desc: Speak with Theo
detail: Theo  a self-proclaimed young researcher  is eager to study everything about the Charon. Lucky you, you've been chosen as his very first case study.

name: Little Researcher
desc: Speak with Theo
detail: You run into Theo again near the sewer entrance. Might as well hear what curious topic he's chasing this time.

name: Little Researcher
desc: Speak with Theo
detail: You come across Theo again near Hypnos' House. Best hear what strange notion he's chasing this time.

name: A New Theatrical Experience
desc: Speak to the friendly troupe member

name: Where It All Begins Again
desc: Lunosmith seems to want a word with you

name: Master of Atlasian Aesthetics
desc: Track down the voice

name: The Melancholy of Violetta
desc: Go with Fane to meet his teacher
detail: A flamboyant man bars your way, insisting his teacher awaits. Follow him and see what's afoot.

name: Scars That Won't Fade
desc: Hear Lars out
detail: A boy named Lars wants your help. Hear him out.

name: The Sorrows of Miss Crate
desc: Find the source of the strange singing
detail: Eerie singing floats from a nearby street corner. Muster your courage and seek out its source.

name: Set Sail Through a Sleepless Night
episode: Set Sail Through a Sleepless Night
desc: Connect the dots and trace the threads to the hidden truth
detail: Your leads all point to a kidnapping and arson that occurred sixteen years ago. Follow the clues  and uncover the truth buried beneath it all.

name: A Cat's Thanks
desc: Check on the lonely stray
detail: You spot the stray loitering near the square again. It seems to recognise you  and lets out a distant miaow.

name: Phoxhunter 101
desc: Try your first assignment  Commission: Hedge is a good place to begin.
detail: Complete Commission: Hedge once

name: Tutorial Quest: Covert Commissions
desc: Complete Covert Commission: [Truffle and Filbert]
detail: Complete [Truffle and Filbert]'s Covert Commission to obtain their Thoughts

name: The Grace of a God
desc: Head into the Gritblight Expanse
detail: A rambling old man stops you with cryptic talk. He has a commission for you.

name: When the Stars Shine Bright
desc: Accompany Zhao Qian to collect the goods
detail: Near EverSpring's gate, raised voices echo from afar. Turns out Starweaver trade in Huaxu is under threat from the Scourge of Zhuyin. If you have time, lend Zhao Qian a hand.

name: Beyond Dafeng's Reach
desc: Search for the "treasure" near the shipwreck
detail: A strange man stops you in the black market. He seems to know the source of that voice in your head. Hear what he has to say.

name: Where the Osmanthus Bloomed
desc: Where the Osmanthus Bloomed
detail: Snow heard about a stall near Mistwharf that sells excellent osmanthus cakes. Go take a look with her.

name: The Joy of Craft
desc: Head to the location pointed out by the Mechanical Nexus
detail: A strange tremor runs through the Mechanical Nexus you carry, as though pointing you towards something. Follow its guidance and head to the indicated location.

name: What He Held Onto
desc: Visit Twilight Ravine to see what's going on
detail: Lately, some Huaxu locals have reported sudden chills down their backs while passing through Twilight Ravine  likely the work of a Wishen. Bring Snow to investigate the area.
